metadata.name: DisOrder #62
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

metadata.name: Point(); Line(); Plane(); #203
metadata.description:
The title of this piece is a reference to Wassily Kandisky's book "Point and Line to Plane" (1926).

Eight points are placed at random positions, assigned a color and direction, and moved, to become lines. These lines are then translated to form planes.

This idea was already formulated by Aristotle: "a line by its motion produces a surface, and a point by its motion a line".

This simple algorithm creates an interesting variety of compositions, all unique and recognizable.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be exported by pressing "s".

PNG exports can be obtained by pressing "1" (3300×1900) or "2" (6600×3800).

metadata.description:

Goodbye.

Time to move on.

#tezosartweek

metadata.name: Grid Meditations #57
metadata.description:
The grid is the ultimate tool of abstraction. 

The grid rejects any imitation of depth.

The grid exposes the true nature of the canvas as a two-dimensional surface.  

The grid both imposes order and allows for the legibility of disorder.

metadata.name: Happenings #50
metadata.description:
Inspired by the chaos and imperfectly beautiful dynamics of parenting and life, 'Happenings' is the embodiment of the messiness, the unexpected and playful experiences that allow for the greatest depths of connection with our children.

Our intention was to evoke our deepest and most personal feelings as parents of young ones navigating the challenges of the pandemic while immersing ourselves in the Web3 arena.

This collection is Jimena + Marcos’ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: Bloody Bear #122
metadata.description:
It is very painful to be in a bear market at the moment. Getting through it required a lot of patience. I hope we can get through it soon.

Besides that, I also created a generative artwork that I gave away for free to collectors. Thank You
